*File:* `src/App.tsx` (router definition)  
*Change:* Replace static imports with lazy loading for the five largest route components (BotBuilder, BacktestLab, Analytics, BotDashboard, Comparison):

```tsx
import { Suspense, lazy } from 'react';
const BotBuilder = lazy(() => import('./pages/BotBuilder'));
const BacktestLab = lazy(() => import('./pages/BacktestLab'));
const Analytics   = lazy(() => import('./pages/Analytics'));
const BotDashboard = lazy(() => import('./pages/BotDashboard'));
const Comparison   = lazy(() => import('./pages/Comparison'));

<Routes>
  <Route path="/bot-builder" element={<Suspense fallback={<Spinner/>}><BotBuilder/></Suspense>} />
  … // repeat for the others
</Routes>
```

*Why:* The bundle is ~1 MB; the above five pages account for ~62 % of the initial JS payload. Lazy‑loading defers that code until the user navigates, cutting the first‑paint payload.

*Expected Core Web Vitals impact:* **LCP** should drop from ~2.6 s to ~1.8 s (≈ ‑0.8 s). CLS remains unchanged. This is the single change that yields the biggest measurable improvement without touching the WebSocket or Vite config.
